  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed for most operating points but one validation result (low-flow, high-speed condition) relies on qualitative characterisation of inherent variability rather than a structured UQ node. Full 13-factor assessment completed; decision: Accepted at reduced confidence.",
