    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU2 VAD hemolysis prediction is accepted at reduced confidence. Monte Carlo UQ is performed for four of five operating points and all 13 credibility factors have been addressed. Achieved levels fall below required levels for all seven assessed factors, and six factors carry epistemic gap flags. The low-flow high-speed validation result relies on qualitative characterisation of aleatory variability rather than a structured UQ node; this is noted as a residual gap. The overall package is accepted with the condition that structured UQ is completed for the low-flow high-speed operating point prior to regulatory submission.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
